HEADWORD: Saddle-backed
<hw>Sad"dle-backed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the outline of the upper part concave like the seat of a
saddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a low back and high neck, as a
horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saddlebags</ent>⟦br⟧
